-- ft.page: How To Create Developer App On Github

-- ft.markdown:

For Oauth Authentication using Github first of all a developer needs to 
create a new app on github. Follow steps given below to create a new 
app on github.

-- ft.markdown:

From the right side of your github top bar. Click on profile picture 
then it will open drop down. From the drop down click on `Settings`.

-- ft.image:
src: $assets.files.static.images.auth.github.github-app-1.png
align: center

-- ft.markdown:

From your Settings page. Scroll down and on your left side menu click on 
`Developer Settings` given at the end.

-- ft.image:
src: $assets.files.static.images.auth.github.github-app-2.png
align: center

-- ft.markdown:

From Developer Setting page click on `OAuth Apps` to create new App

-- ft.image:
src: $assets.files.static.images.auth.github.github-app-3.png
align: center

-- ft.markdown:

Here you can get Client Id and Client Secret that you can save in somewhere 
that will be used to access the application.

-- ft.markdown:

Also fill in the Homepage Url and Authorization callback url. 
Authorization callback url is the url where github will redirect users 
with code and state after login.

-- ft.image:
src: $assets.files.static.images.auth.github.github-app-4.png
align: center
